# AGENTS_REFERENCE_V2

## Rule Format
- `<ID> | <scope> | <level> | <instruction>`
- Precedence: `task-specific > scope-specific > global`
- `AGENTS_REFERENCE_V2` is non-normative. `AGENTS_V2` is normative.

## Module Map
- M01 | codex-auth/** | INFO | Rust CLI (`cargo`), installer: `codex-auth/scripts/install.sh`, runtime watcher: `codex-auth watch`.
- M02 | codex-sessions/** | INFO | Rust CLI (`cargo`), installer: `codex-sessions/scripts/install.sh`, runtime watcher: `codex-sessions watch thread-titles`.
- M03 | codex-remote/** | INFO | TypeScript CLI (`npm`), installer: `codex-remote/scripts/install.sh`, bot lifecycle: `codex-remote start|stop|status|restart|logs`.
- M04 | codex-menubar/** | INFO | Swift macOS app (`swift build`), installer/launcher: `codex-menubar/scripts/install.sh`.
- M05 | codex-agents/** | INFO | Bash CLI, installer: `codex-agents/scripts/install.sh`, command surface via `scripts/codex-agents`.
- M06 | voice/** | INFO | Android app (Gradle, package `com.sanogueralorenzo.voice`).
- M07 | overlay/** | INFO | Android app (Gradle, package `com.sanogueralorenzo.overlay`).
- M08 | site/** | INFO | Hugo static site (`hugo --minify`), CI deploy via `.github/workflows/hugo.yml`.

## Check Fallbacks
- F01 | rust-check | SHOULD | If `cargo test` is blocked by env/tooling, fallback to `cargo check`; report blocker and failed command.
- F02 | ts-check | SHOULD | If `npm run typecheck && npm run build` fails from dependency drift, run `npm install` once then retry.
- F03 | android-check | SHOULD | If no Android device is available, run `:app:assembleDebug` and report missing device for install/launch.
- F04 | site-check | SHOULD | If `hugo` is unavailable, report missing binary and next command to install/verify.

## Install-Gate Decision
- G01 | changed-paths | SHOULD | Evaluate docs-only short-circuit first.
- G02 | changed-paths | SHOULD | Apply root install gate only for install-gated codex modules (`auth/sessions/remote/menubar`).
- G03 | changed-paths | SHOULD | Never apply root install gate for Android-only or site-only changes.
- G04 | changed-paths | SHOULD | For mixed changes, run narrow checks first, then required module installs, then root install gate if active.

## Optional Architecture Guidance
- A01 | * | SHOULD | Prefer explicit code paths and feature-scoped modules.
- A02 | android | SHOULD | Prefer child feature `NavHost` when a feature owns multi-screen state.
- A03 | android | SHOULD | Keep Compose + Mavericks `ViewModel` + Mavericks `State` boundaries explicit.
- A04 | web/ts-app | SHOULD | Keep UI state deterministic with one source of truth per feature.
- A05 | typescript | SHOULD | Keep strict typing and justify any `any` inline.
- A06 | telegram-bot | SHOULD | Keep handlers thin; isolate side-effecting business logic in services.
- A07 | orchestration | SHOULD | Keep workflows idempotent/resumable with explicit step contracts and persisted checkpoints.

## Reporting
- R01 | validation-report | SHOULD | Report checks run, checks skipped, and blockers with exact commands.
- R02 | install-report | SHOULD | Report which install gate fired and which install/launch commands were executed.
- R03 | links | SHOULD | Return direct links for PR/Jira/Slack artifacts when touched.
